{"word":"H6035 - עָנָו - ʻânâv - aw-nawv' - Humble","slug":"H6035","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עָנָו</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻânâv"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-nawv'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Humble"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E2;&#x05E0;&#x05D9;&#x05D5;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E2;&#x05E0;&#x05D5; - &#x201B;a&#x0302;na&#x0302;v  &#x201B;a&#x0302;na&#x0302;yv</b> - <i>aw-nawv', aw-nawv'</i><p/>The second form is by intermixture with <a href=\"#/H6041\">H6041</a>; from <a href=\"#/H6031\">H6031</a>; <i>depressed</i> (figuratively), in mind (<i>gentle</i>) or circumstances (<i>needy</i>, especially <i>saintly</i>): - humble, lowly, meek, poor`. Compare <a href=\"#/H6041\">H6041</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6031\">H6031</a>, <a href=\"#/H6037\">H6037</a>, <a href=\"#/H6038\">H6038</a>, <a href=\"#/H6039\">H6039</a>, <a href=\"#/H6040\">H6040</a>, <a href=\"#/H6041\">H6041</a>, <a href=\"#/H8589\">H8589</a>"}]}